1
00:00:00,050 --> 00:00:03,385
The Seller registers a represented receivable.

2
00:00:03,385 --> 00:00:07,942
Open RFQ stays blocked until both attestations exist.

3
00:00:07,942 --> 00:00:12,838
Compliance and Risk then issue separate, scoped attestations.

4
00:00:12,838 --> 00:00:16,888
Compliance records eligibility; Risk records the tier.

5
00:00:16,888 --> 00:00:20,273
Both are now recorded, so the Seller can open RFQ.

6
00:00:20,273 --> 00:00:26,289
The Seller derives certificates and creates one private request for each invited Funder.

7
00:00:26,289 --> 00:00:36,757
These are real Daml contracts with role-specific signatories and observers; during bidding, raw Debtor identity is limited to Seller and Compliance.
